Open source projects and services used or integrated:

- FastHTML
  https://fastht.ml/
  Python web framework used for routing, HTML generation, and HTMX integration.

- MonsterUI
  https://github.com/AnswerDotAI/MonsterUI
  UI framework for FastHTML used for components, styling, and Markdown rendering.

- HTMX
  https://htmx.org/
  Used for lightweight loading/polling interactions.

- SQLite
  https://sqlite.org/
  Embedded database used for summary caching, metadata, settings, and rate-limit state.

- Simon Willison's llm-hacker-news
  https://github.com/simonw/llm-hacker-news
  Used for Hacker News comment-thread processing/formatting.

- Simon Willison's llm
  https://llm.datasette.io/
  Installed as a dependency of llm-hacker-news. This application currently calls OpenRouter directly rather than using llm as the model execution layer.

- Mistletoe / mistlefoot
  https://github.com/miyuchina/mistletoe
  Markdown parsing/rendering dependency used through MonsterUI.

- OpenRouter
  https://openrouter.ai/
  Upstream LLM API used for summary generation.

- Hacker News APIs
  Official Firebase API: https://github.com/HackerNews/API
  Algolia HN API: https://hn.algolia.com/api
  Used for item validation and comment retrieval.

- Python requests
  https://requests.readthedocs.io/
  Used for outbound HTTP requests.

- python-dotenv is listed as a dependency from earlier development, though the app currently reads .env directly for compatibility with both KEY=value and KEY: value formats.
